    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/7",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">As in single-name options, in the simplest of implementations, the asset price processes are modeled with lognormal processes endowed with a correlation matrix. In more sophisticated implementations, to account for the volatility smile, some versions of stochastic volatility models are often used. One may even include some form of default component in the asset price. However, in these more complex models, the modeling of correlation and its estimation become more complex as well.</p>",
      "page": 312,
      "polygon": [
